      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">NIST Handbook 44 is adopted by many state, local, and some federal
                weights and measures authorities to apply to commercial weighing and measuring
                equipment and associated equipment and for use in applications for law enforcement
                and the collection of statistical information by government agencies. This 2024
                edition includes amendments made through the Committee on Specifications and
                Tolerances of the National Conference on Weights and Measures (NCWM) with technical
                guidance from the Office of Weights and Measures (OWM) of the National Institute of
                Standards and Technology (NIST) and input from weights and measures officials and
                industry representatives. These amendments were adopted by the NCWM at its 108th
                Annual Meeting in July 2023.</abstract>
